

    Summary
    ADHD.pl for some reason is going to set the limit of 4GB for all virtual RPAs. The result returned by os_services.sh to ADHD.pl will always be "vGEN" for virtual RPA machines. This is the condition to lower the RPA log bundle size.
    Editing the tweak t_IC_maxRPAsInfoSize and restarting the installation server may help in providing a temporary relief. Once RPA is rebooted the tweak will be reset.


    observations from code

    Installation Server 
    Collection happens in CollectSystemInformationCommand  @ http://10.76.67.9:8080/source/xref/RP4VM_rel_5_2_2_0_0/src/management/com.kashya.recoverpoint.installation.server/src/main/java/com/kashya/installation/server/commands/global/CollectSystemInformationCommand.java
    The Tweak IC_MAX_RPAS_INFO_SIZE_TWEAK is initialized as t_IC_MAX_RPA_INFO_SIZE_TWEAK @ http://10.76.67.9:8080/source/xref/RP=4VM_rel_5_2_2_0_0/src/management/com.kashya.recoverpoint.installation.server/src/main/java/com/kashya/installation/server/EnvironmentConstants.java#202
    The tweak is referenced in: 
    Review validateSizeLimit @ http://10.76.67.9:8080/source/s?refs=validateSizeLimit&project=RP4VM_rel_5_2_2_0_0
    Review isEnoughSpaceInRP @ http://10.76.67.9:8080/source/s?refs=isEnoughFreeSpaceOnRPA&project=RP4VM_rel_5_2_2_0_0

    ADHD.pl is setup to run every reboot 
    Check rc.local @ http://10.76.67.9:8080/source/xref/RP4VM_rel_5_2_2_0_0/src/installation/distribution/rc.local#99 
    ADHD.pl will use os_Services.sh @ http://10.76.67.9:8080/source/xref/RP4VM_rel_5_2_2_0_0/src/installation/distribution/os_services/os_services.sh?r=564d1a16#1002 
    and will reduce the log file size tweak to 4 GB if the Generation returned is "vGEN" which stands for "virtual generation" set for RP4VMs always

    check here http://10.76.67.9:8080/source/xref/RP4VM_rel_5_2_2_0_0/src/installation/distribution/os_services/os_services.sh?r=564d1a16#985 in os_services.sh
